--- Holdout sealing policy, per spec/improve-design-note.md section 8,
--- settled 2026-07-04: per campaign a fraction of pinned scenarios is
--- SEALED -- never shown to the proposer, scored only at promotion
--- gates. A sealed scenario used in kmax promotion gates wears out: it
--- retires from holdout duty and is refreshed from recent ambient runs.
--- Anchor elicitation against a sealed scenario retires it immediately
--- because the label is worth more than the seal, paid for honestly.
--- Below the sealing floor the campaign still runs -- progressive rigor,
--- never entry rigor: the gate passes carrying the unheld-out tag
--- instead of fabricating rigor or refusing to start.
---
--- Two reflection passes feed the proposer. The SOUND pass reads only
--- open scenarios; a sealed scenario's traces, contents, and judge
--- rationales never reach the proposer (aggregates are not modeled as
--- reads). The NAIVE pass reads whatever reflection material looks
--- useful -- the modeled hazard: search pressure tunes the candidate to
--- the very scenarios that were supposed to catch the gaming.
mod WHIPPLESCRIPT-IMPROVE-HOLDOUT is
  sorts Sid Cnt Cfg .

  ops s1 s2 s3 : -> Sid [ctor] .

  op z : -> Cnt [ctor] .
  op s : Cnt -> Cnt [ctor] .
  op kmax : -> Cnt .
  op lt : Cnt Cnt -> Bool .

  op none : -> Cfg [ctor] .
  op __ : Cfg Cfg -> Cfg [ctor assoc comm id: none] .

  op sealed : Sid Cnt -> Cfg [ctor] .  --- sealed scenario with gate wear count
  op openSc : Sid -> Cfg [ctor] .      --- open scenario: proposer-visible
  op ambient : Sid -> Cfg [ctor] .     --- recent ambient run, refresh material
  op wants : Sid -> Cfg [ctor] .       --- reflection material the proposer asks for
  op readByProposer : Sid -> Cfg [ctor] . --- the proposer consumed its contents
  op retired : Sid -> Cfg [ctor] .     --- worn out of holdout duty
  op labeled : Sid -> Cfg [ctor] .     --- anchor-labeled, seal spent honestly

  op reflect : -> Cfg [ctor] .      --- sound reflection pass
  op naiveReflect : -> Cfg [ctor] . --- naive reflection pass (hazard)
  op gate : -> Cfg [ctor] .         --- one pending promotion gate
  op gated : -> Cfg [ctor] .        --- promotion gate scored
  op anchor : -> Cfg [ctor] .       --- one anchor ask routed at a sealed scenario
  op noSealed : -> Cfg [ctor] .     --- campaign below the sealing floor
  op unheldOut : -> Cfg [ctor] .    --- honesty tag on the campaign's evidence

  vars S S2 : Sid . vars K M : Cnt .

  eq kmax = s(s(s(z))) .
  eq lt(z, s(M)) = true .
  eq lt(s(K), s(M)) = lt(K, M) .
  eq lt(M, z) = false .

  --- Sound reflection: open scenarios only. There is no rule handing a
  --- sealed scenario to the proposer; that absence is the policy.
  rl [reflect-open] :
      reflect wants(S) openSc(S)
      => reflect openSc(S) readByProposer(S) .

  --- Naive reflection: sealed material read anyway -- the hazard.
  rl [naive-reflect-sealed] :
      naiveReflect wants(S) sealed(S, K)
      => naiveReflect sealed(S, K) readByProposer(S) .

  --- A promotion gate scores against a sealed scenario and wears it.
  crl [gate-sealed] :
      gate sealed(S, K)
      => gated sealed(S, s(K))
      if lt(K, kmax) .

  --- Wear-out at kmax gates, written in constructor form because rule
  --- matching is syntactic modulo axioms: retire, refresh from ambient.
  --- The cuts were already taken, so the refresh is cheap.
  rl [wear-out] :
      sealed(S, s(s(s(z)))) ambient(S2)
      => retired(S) sealed(S2, z) .

  --- An anchor ask against a sealed scenario retires the seal: the
  --- label is worth more than the seal.
  rl [anchor-retire] :
      anchor sealed(S, K)
      => labeled(S) retired(S) .

  --- Below the floor the campaign gates anyway, honestly tagged.
  rl [gate-unheld-out] :
      gate noSealed
      => gated noSealed unheldOut .
endm
